dd the message key header, while the KafkaNullConverter might need a method to convert KafkaNull to null. I also want to ensure the DefaultMessageConverterHelper is set up for batch header prunes, and there are runtime hints for properties.\\\\n\\\\nI have to think about merging broker configurations, provisioning topics, and using Spring Integration's DirectChannel for binding producers and consumers. I wonder how to effectively configure this with Spring Boot and whether additional dependencies will be necessary.\\\"}]}\"}, {\"type\": \"toolCall\", \"id\": \"call_a8M5R2DiKWh874KMXgNZBIni|fc_007c0874e003665f016a404189a12c8194a82f2c2bb4e6449b\", \"name\": \"bash\", \"arguments\": {\"command\": \"find tests/src/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka/5.0.1 -maxdepth 3 -type f -print -exec grep -Hn \\\"\\\" {} \\\\; | head -120; rg -n \\\"ApplicationContextRunner|SpringApplication|EmbeddedKafka|KafkaTemplate|DefaultKafkaProducerFactory|KafkaTestUtils\\\" tests/src/org.springframework.cloud -S\", \"timeout\": 10}}], \"api\": \"openai-responses\", \"provider\": \"OCA\", \"model\": \"oca/gpt-5.5\", \"usage\": {\"input\": 540, \"output\": 751, \"cacheRead\": 26624, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"totalTokens\": 27915, \"cost\": {\"input\": 0, \"output\": 0, \"cacheRead\": 0, \"cacheWrite\": 0, \"total\": 0}}, \"stopReason\": \"toolUse\", \"timestamp\": 1782595967751, \"responseId\": \"resp_007c0874e003665f016a40418037b88194a02a61f5c6e7f430\"}}\n5475:[tool-exec] start id=call_a8M5R2DiKWh874KMXgNZBIni|fc_007c0874e003665f016a404189a12c8194a82f2c2bb4e6449b name=bash args={\"command\": \"find tests/src/org.springframework.cloud/spring-cloud-stream-binder-kafka/5.0.1 -maxdepth 3 -type f -print -exec grep -Hn \\\"\\\" {} \\\\; | head -120; rg -n \\\"ApplicationContextRunner|SpringApplication|EmbeddedKafka|KafkaTemplate|DefaultKafkaProducerFactory|KafkaTestUtils\\\" tests/src/org.springframework.cloud -S\", \"timeout\": 10}\n5784:  tests/src/org.springframework.cloud/spri